   It was an extraordinary scene in the palace of Westminster on Wednesday night as one by one her [Thatcher] own Cabinet members trooped sheepishly into Thatcher's office and told her, in their chosen code, that they "couldn't support her over the weekend" in the second round of secret balloting on the party's leadership.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   They were the ones who would each ditch their closest friends in order to support the other: Reagan when overruling Jeane Kirkpatrick's objections to the Falklands campaign, and Thatcher when blocking her own right wing's protests at the U.S. bombing of Libya from British bases.
